1300SMILES Stadium is one of nine major sporting and entertainment facilities owned and operated by Stadiums Queensland. Stadiums Queensland (SQ) has been established by the Queensland Government to manage, operate and promote the use of the State’s major sports, recreation and leisure facilities.  SQ is a statutory body overseen by a Board of Directors and has responsibility for the following venues:

Brisbane Cricket Ground (The Gabba);
Suncorp Stadium;
Sleeman Sports Complex;
Brisbane Entertainment Centre; 
Queensland Sports and Athletic Centre;
Skilled Park;
Queensland Tennis Centre;
Metricon Stadium; and
1300SMILES Stadium.

Source: This is an extract from the company's own website.
